atom.name: ENUS
atom.value:
The name of the storage pool. Maximum length: 20 characters.

For the purpose of object replication, storage is organized into storage pools. A storage pool is a logical grouping of Storage Nodes or Archive Nodes.

When configuring ILM rules, there is a one to one relationship between copies, Storage Nodes, and Archive Nodes. For each copy required by an ILM rule, there must be a corresponding Storage Node or Archive Node in the selected storage pool.

atom.name: ENUS
atom.value: The total number of Archive Nodes in the storage pool. Archive Nodes and Storage Nodes cannot be configured in the same storage pool.

atom.name: ENUS
atom.value: The total number of Storage Nodes in the storage pool. An ILM rule allows one copy for each Storage Node or Archive Node in a storage pool.

atom.name: ENUS
atom.value: The total amount of installed storage capacity for the storage pool.

atom.name: ENUS
atom.value: The total amount of installed storage capacity that has been consumed. This value is derived from the difference between Installed capacity and Usable capacity.

atom.name: ENUS
atom.value: The total amount of installed storage capacity that is currently usable for the storage pool.
